<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<meta name="robots" content="noindex,nofollow">
<meta name="theme-color" content="#1a1a2e">
<title>Service Terms — Iron Tiger Digital × Keith Zars Pools</title>

<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 64 64'%3E%3Crect width='64' height='64' rx='12' fill='%2310b981'/%3E%3Ctext x='32' y='44' font-family='system-ui' font-size='32' font-weight='800' text-anchor='middle' fill='%23fff'%3EITD%3C/text%3E%3C/svg%3E">

<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Plus+Jakarta+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap">

<style>
:root {
  --green: #10b981;
  --green-dark: #059669;
  --dark: #1a1a2e;
  --gray: #5a5a5a;
  --light: #f7faf9;
  --border: #d2ecdf;
  --badge-bg: #e6f7ef;
  --badge-color: #059669;
  --text: #222;
}
* { box-sizing: border-box; }
body {
  font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
  margin: 0;
  background: var(--light);
  color: var(--dark);
  line-height: 1.7;
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
}
.wrap { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.25rem 4rem; }

/* ─── HEADER ─── */
header {
  background: var(--dark);
  color: #fff;
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  text-align: center;
  border-bottom: 4px solid var(--green);
}
header .eyebrow {
  font-size: .7rem;
  letter-spacing: .15em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  opacity: .7;
  margin-bottom: .3rem;
}
header h1 {
  margin: 0;
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -.01em;
}
header .sub {
  margin: .4rem 0 0;
  font-size: .8rem;
  opacity: .6;
}

/* ─── BACK LINK ─── */
.back-link {
  display: block;
  margin: 1.25rem 0 .5rem;
  font-size: .82rem;
  color: var(--green-dark);
  text-decoration: none;
  font-weight: 600;
}
.back-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

/* ─── INTRO BOX ─── */
.intro-box {
  background: var(--badge-bg);
  border: 1.5px solid var(--green);
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 1.1rem 1.3rem;
  margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  font-size: .9rem;
  color: var(--text);
  line-height: 1.6;
}
.intro-box strong { color: var(--green-dark); }

/* ─── CLAUSE SECTIONS ─── */
.terms-doc {
  background: #fff;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 14px;
  padding: 2rem 1.75rem;
  box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,.04);
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
}
.terms-doc .doc-title {
  font-size: .7rem;
  letter-spacing: .14em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--gray);
  font-weight: 700;
  padding-bottom: .75rem;
  border-bottom: 1.5px solid var(--border);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.clause {
  margin-bottom: 1.35rem;
  padding-bottom: 1.35rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.clause:last-of-type {
  margin-bottom: 0;
  padding-bottom: 0;
  border-bottom: none;
}
.clause .cl-num {
  font-size: .68rem;
  font-weight: 800;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: .12em;
  color: var(--green-dark);
  margin-bottom: .2rem;
}
.clause .cl-head {
  font-size: .97rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--dark);
  margin-bottom: .35rem;
}
.clause .cl-body {
  font-size: .88rem;
  color: var(--gray);
  line-height: 1.7;
}
.clause .cl-body strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }
.clause .cl-body em { color: var(--text); }

/* ─── SIGNATURE BLOCK ─── */
.sig-block {
  margin-top: 2rem;
  padding-top: 1.5rem;
  border-top: 1.5px solid var(--border);
}
.sig-block .sig-title {
  font-size: .72rem;
  letter-spacing: .12em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--gray);
  font-weight: 700;
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
}
.sig-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 2rem;
}
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .sig-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; }
}
.sig-party-name {
  font-size: .82rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: .07em;
  color: var(--dark);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}
.sig-line {
  border-bottom: 1.5px solid #999;
  margin-bottom: .35rem;
  height: 36px;
}
.sig-line-label {
  font-size: .72rem;
  color: var(--gray);
  letter-spacing: .04em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  font-weight: 600;
  margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
}

/* ─── FOOTER ─── */
footer {
  text-align: center;
  font-size: .78rem;
  color: var(--gray);
  margin-top: 2.5rem;
  padding-top: 1.25rem;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
}
footer strong { color: var(--green-dark); }
.date-badge {
  display: inline-block;
  background: var(--badge-bg);
  color: var(--badge-color);
  padding: .15rem .55rem;
  border-radius: 999px;
  font-size: .72rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: .04em;
}

@media print {
  body { background: #fff; }
  .wrap { padding-bottom: 1rem; }
  .back-link { display: none; }
  .sig-line { border-bottom: 1.5px solid #333; }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <div class="eyebrow">Iron Tiger Digital × Keith Zars Pools</div>
  <h1>Lead Generation Service Terms</h1>
  <div class="sub">These terms are attached to the Lead Generation Proposal dated May 2026</div>
</header>

<div class="wrap">

<a class="back-link" href="keith-zars.html">← Back to Proposal</a>

<div class="intro-box">
  These Service Terms govern the lead generation arrangement between <strong>Costa Demetral d/b/a Iron Tiger Digital</strong> ("Provider") and <strong>Keith Zars Pools</strong> ("Client"). They are plain-language and designed to be understood without a lawyer. The Proposal document covers the ROI math, payment mechanics, and lead quality standards. These Terms cover the binding operating rules both parties agree to. Together, the Proposal and these Terms form the complete agreement.
</div>

<!-- ─── CFO SUMMARY ─── -->
<div style="background:#fff;border:1.5px solid var(--border);border-radius:12px;padding:1.25rem 1.4rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
  <div style="font-size:.7rem;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.13em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gray);margin-bottom:.85rem;">Key Business Terms — At a Glance</div>
  <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:.88rem;">
    <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);width:38%;">Price</td>
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;color:var(--gray);">$500 per lead — no retainer, no minimums</td>
    </tr>
    <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);">Billing</td>
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;color:var(--gray);">Net-15 from invoice date, weekly ACH</td>
    </tr>
    <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);">Pilot Exit</td>
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;color:var(--gray);">If fewer than 3 of first 10 leads book a consult — exit free, no penalties. Period extends to 60 days if 10 leads not delivered by day 30 (Section 2)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);">Weekly Lead Cap</td>
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;color:var(--gray);"><strong style="color:var(--dark);">[__] leads/week</strong> — hard budget ceiling, agreed at signing (Section 7)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);">Disputes</td>
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;color:var(--gray);">14-day window. Credit on next invoice. No cash refunds (Section 8)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);">Termination</td>
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;color:var(--gray);">30 days written notice. No penalties, no wind-down (Section 11)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);">Max Liability</td>
      <td style="padding:.55rem 0;color:var(--gray);">Capped at fees paid in the prior 30 days (Section 13)</td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</div>

<div class="terms-doc">
  <div class="doc-title">Iron Tiger Digital — Lead Generation Service Terms · May 2026</div>


  <!-- ─── 1. PARTIES ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 1</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Parties &amp; Effective Date</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      This Lead Generation Service Agreement ("Agreement") is entered into as of <strong>[Date]</strong> by and between <strong>Costa Demetral d/b/a Iron Tiger Digital</strong>, a sole proprietor operating as Iron Tiger Digital, with principal business address at <strong>[Business Address]</strong>, email: costa@irontigerleads.com, phone: (225) 535-4918 ("Provider"), and <strong>Keith Zars Pools</strong> ("Client"). Provider and Client are each referred to individually as a "Party" and collectively as the "Parties."
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 2. PILOT PERIOD ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 2</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Pilot Period &amp; Exit Clause</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      <strong>Pilot Period.</strong> The first 30 days of this Agreement constitute a Pilot Period. During the Pilot Period, Provider will deliver up to ten (10) Leads at the standard rate of $500 per Lead. No retainer or minimum purchase is required.<br><br>
      <strong>Pilot Exit.</strong> If fewer than three (3) of the first ten (10) Leads delivered result in a Booked Appointment within thirty (30) days of the first Lead delivery, Client may terminate this Agreement immediately upon written notice to Provider with no further financial obligation beyond Leads already invoiced and unpaid. No wind-down fees, penalties, or additional invoices will apply. If three (3) or more Booked Appointments are confirmed within the Pilot Period, the Agreement continues automatically on a month-to-month basis per Section 11.<br><br>
      <strong>"Booked Appointment" defined.</strong> A Booked Appointment means a confirmed, scheduled on-site consultation or project estimate with the homeowner, communicated to Provider by Client via email within seven (7) days of the appointment occurring. Client agrees to report Booked Appointments in good faith as a condition of invoking the Pilot Exit clause. Provider may request written verification of appointment scheduling (such as a confirmation email or calendar entry) within seven (7) business days of Client invoking the Pilot Exit clause, and Client will provide such verification within five (5) business days of the request.<br><br>
      <strong>Pilot Period extension.</strong> If Provider has not delivered ten (10) Leads by day thirty (30) of the Pilot Period, the Pilot Period will automatically extend until the tenth Lead is delivered, up to a maximum of sixty (60) days from the start date. If ten (10) Leads have not been delivered by day sixty (60), the standard month-to-month agreement begins automatically, and the exit threshold is prorated: Client may invoke the exit clause if fewer than 30% of Leads delivered by day sixty (60) resulted in a Booked Appointment.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 3. DEFINITIONS ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 3</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Lead Definition</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      A <strong>"Lead"</strong> is an inbound form submission or phone inquiry originating from Provider's lead generation website(s), from a homeowner located within the agreed Service Territory, expressing genuine interest in new pool construction or major pool renovation. A valid Lead must include: (a) a full name, (b) a working contact phone number, and (c) a service address within the Service Territory. Leads that fail to meet these criteria are subject to the dispute process in Section 8.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 4. DELIVERY ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 4</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Delivery Process</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      Provider will deliver each Lead to Client via email within <strong>one (1) hour</strong> of receipt during business hours (8 AM–8 PM CT Mon–Fri, 10 AM–5 PM CT Sat–Sun). Each delivery will include, to the extent available: full name, phone number, email address, service address, project description, and submission timestamp. Leads received outside business hours may be delivered the following morning. For any phone Lead disputed under Section 8, Provider will supply the call recording within <strong>three (3) business days</strong> of a written request.<br><br>
      <strong>Audit access.</strong> Client may at any time request a written log of all Leads delivered under this Agreement. Provider will supply a complete delivery log within five (5) business days of a written request.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 5. SERVICE TERRITORY ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 5</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Service Territory</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      Provider will deliver Leads originating from homeowners located within <strong>150 miles of San Antonio, Texas</strong>, which includes but is not limited to: San Antonio metro, New Braunfels, Corpus Christi, Seguin, Boerne, Kerrville, and surrounding communities. Leads from addresses clearly outside this territory are disputable under Section 8.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 6. EXCLUSIVITY + IP ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 6</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Exclusivity &amp; Intellectual Property</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      Once a Lead is delivered to Client, Provider will not sell, transfer, or share that same Lead with any other contractor or third party. Client acknowledges that homeowners may independently contact other contractors; however, Provider's exclusive obligation is to deliver each Lead to Client only through Provider's distribution channels.<br><br>
      <strong>IP ownership.</strong> All websites, domain names, content, and organic search rankings used to generate Leads remain the sole property of Provider at all times. This Agreement does not transfer, license, or assign any ownership in Provider's websites or digital assets to Client. Termination of this Agreement does not grant Client any right to replicate or acquire those assets.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 7. FEES + PAYMENT ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 7</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Fees &amp; Payment</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      Client agrees to pay Provider <strong>$500 (USD) per delivered Lead</strong>. Provider will issue a weekly invoice every Friday covering all Leads delivered during that calendar week. Payment is due <strong>Net-15</strong> from the invoice date via ACH bank transfer. There is no setup fee, no monthly retainer, and no minimum volume commitment.<br><br>
      <strong>Weekly lead cap.</strong> Provider will deliver no more than <strong>[__] Leads per calendar week</strong> unless both Parties agree in writing to adjust the cap. This cap exists to allow Client's team to manage lead flow and follow-up quality. Leads in excess of the cap in a given week will roll to the following week.<br><br>
      <strong>W-9.</strong> Provider will supply a completed IRS Form W-9 to Client prior to the first invoice being issued. This enables Client to set up Iron Tiger Digital as a vendor in its accounts payable system without delay.<br><br>
      Invoices unpaid after 30 days from the due date may accrue interest at 1.5% per month on the outstanding balance. Client may indicate a preferred payment method (ACH, Bill.com, or Melio) when returning the signed Agreement — Provider will accommodate at no additional cost.<br><br>
      <strong>Rate adjustments.</strong> Provider may adjust the per-lead fee by providing <strong>thirty (30) days written notice</strong> to Client. If Client does not accept the new rate, Client may terminate this Agreement under Section 11 during the notice period with no early-termination penalty.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 8. DISPUTE PROCESS ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 8</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Dispute Process</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      Client must raise any dispute within <strong>fourteen (14) calendar days</strong> of Lead delivery by emailing costa@irontigerleads.com with the Lead name, delivery date, and reason for dispute.<br><br>
      <strong>Eligible dispute reasons:</strong> (a) wrong or disconnected phone number, (b) service address clearly outside the defined territory, or (c) exact duplicate of a Lead already delivered and billed in the same calendar month.<br><br>
      If Provider accepts the dispute, a <strong>credit equal to $500</strong> will be applied to Client's next weekly invoice. No cash refunds will be issued. Disputes not raised within 14 calendar days are deemed waived. Disputes based on failed close, homeowner unavailability, or competitive loss are not eligible.<br><br>
      <strong>Provider response timeline.</strong> Provider will acknowledge any dispute within <strong>three (3) business days</strong> of receipt and will resolve it — either accepting or rejecting with a written explanation — within <strong>ten (10) business days</strong>. A dispute not resolved by Provider within ten (10) business days is deemed accepted and the credit will be applied automatically to the next invoice.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 9. NO CONVERSION GUARANTEE ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 9</div>
    <div class="cl-head">No Conversion Guarantee</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      Provider makes no representation or warranty regarding the conversion rate of Leads. Provider's obligation is to deliver qualified inbound Leads meeting the definition in Section 3. Whether a Lead results in a scheduled appointment, signed contract, or completed job is solely the responsibility of Client's sales and operations team.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 10. CONFIDENTIALITY ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 10</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Confidentiality</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      Each Party agrees to keep Lead data (including homeowner names, addresses, phone numbers, and project details) confidential and to use it solely for the purposes of this Agreement. Client will not resell, share, or distribute Lead data to any third party. Provider will not disclose Client's lead volume, close rates, or pricing to any competitor. This obligation survives termination of this Agreement.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 11. TERM + TERMINATION ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 11</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Term &amp; Termination</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      This Agreement begins on the Effective Date and continues on a <strong>month-to-month basis</strong> following the Pilot Period (Section 2). Either Party may terminate by providing <strong>thirty (30) days written notice</strong> via email to the other Party's address on file. There are no early-termination penalties.<br><br>
      <strong>Upon termination:</strong> (a) Provider will cease delivering Leads; (b) all invoices for Leads delivered prior to the termination effective date remain due and payable per the payment terms in Section 7; (c) any pending disputes will be resolved under Section 8; and (d) each Party will delete or return the other Party's confidential data within <strong>thirty (30) days</strong>. On request, either Party will provide written confirmation that data has been deleted.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 12. FORCE MAJEURE ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 12</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Force Majeure</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      Neither Party will be liable for delays or failures in performance resulting from causes beyond its reasonable control, including but not limited to: algorithm changes by search engines materially reducing lead flow, acts of God, government actions, internet service disruptions, or platform outages. Provider will notify Client in writing within five (5) business days if a force majeure event materially affects Lead delivery volume. During a force majeure period, billing will reflect only Leads actually delivered. Either Party may terminate with immediate written notice if a force majeure event persists for more than sixty (60) days.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 13. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 13</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Limitation of Liability</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      Provider's maximum aggregate liability to Client under this Agreement shall not exceed the <strong>total fees paid by Client to Provider in the thirty (30) days immediately preceding the event giving rise to the claim</strong>. In no event shall either Party be liable to the other for indirect, incidental, consequential, special, or punitive damages, including but not limited to lost profits, lost revenue, or damage to goodwill, even if advised of the possibility of such damages.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 14. TCPA COMPLIANCE ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 14</div>
    <div class="cl-head">TCPA Compliance</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      Provider's lead capture forms obtain prior express written consent under current TCPA and FCC standards, disclosing that the homeowner may be contacted by a licensed pool contractor and may opt out at any time. Client is solely responsible for complying with all applicable telemarketing laws — including TCPA, FCC regulations, the National DNC Registry, and all opt-out obligations — in its own outreach practices.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 15. GOVERNING LAW ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 15</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Governing Law</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      This Agreement is governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the <strong>State of Texas</strong>, without regard to its conflict of law provisions. Any disputes that cannot be resolved informally shall be brought in the state or federal courts located in Bexar County, Texas.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 16. INDEMNIFICATION ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 16</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Indemnification</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      <strong>By Provider.</strong> Provider will indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Client and its officers, employees, and agents from any third-party claims, losses, or liabilities arising directly from Provider's lead capture practices, including any alleged violations of TCPA or applicable law in Provider's opt-in forms and landing pages.<br><br>
      <strong>By Client.</strong> Client will indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Provider and its officers, employees, and agents from any third-party claims, losses, or liabilities arising directly from Client's outreach and communications practices, including compliance with telemarketing laws, the National DNC Registry, and all opt-out obligations once a Lead has been delivered.<br><br>
      Each Party's indemnification obligation is limited to claims arising from its own acts or omissions and does not extend to claims caused by the indemnified Party's negligence or willful misconduct.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 17. ENTIRE AGREEMENT ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 17</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Entire Agreement</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      This Agreement, together with the Lead Generation Proposal dated May 2026, constitutes the entire agreement between the Parties and supersedes all prior negotiations, representations, or agreements, whether written or oral. Modifications must be made in writing and signed by both Parties.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── 18. SEVERABILITY ─── -->
  <div class="clause">
    <div class="cl-num">Section 18</div>
    <div class="cl-head">Severability</div>
    <div class="cl-body">
      If any provision of this Agreement is held to be invalid, illegal, or unenforceable under applicable law, that provision will be deemed modified to the minimum extent necessary to make it enforceable, or if modification is not possible, severed from this Agreement. The remaining provisions will continue in full force and effect.
    </div>
  </div>


  <!-- ─── SIGNATURE BLOCK ─── -->
  <div class="sig-block">
    <div class="sig-title">Signatures — By signing below, each Party agrees to the terms above</div>
    <p style="font-size:.82rem;color:var(--gray);margin:0 0 1.25rem;line-height:1.55;"><strong style="color:var(--text);">Electronic signatures accepted.</strong> Both parties may sign electronically via DocuSign, HelloSign, or by printing, signing, scanning, and returning by email to <strong>costa@irontigerleads.com</strong>. An electronic signature carries the same legal weight as a wet signature under the E-SIGN Act (15 U.S.C. § 7001) and UETA.</p>
    <div class="sig-grid">

      <div>
        <div class="sig-party-name">Iron Tiger Digital (Provider)</div>
        <div class="sig-line"></div>
        <div class="sig-line-label">Signature</div>
        <div class="sig-line"></div>
        <div class="sig-line-label">Printed Name</div>
        <div class="sig-line"></div>
        <div class="sig-line-label">Title</div>
        <div class="sig-line"></div>
        <div class="sig-line-label">Date</div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="sig-party-name">Keith Zars Pools (Client)</div>
        <div class="sig-line"></div>
        <div class="sig-line-label">Signature</div>
        <div class="sig-line"></div>
        <div class="sig-line-label">Printed Name</div>
        <div class="sig-line"></div>
        <div class="sig-line-label">Title</div>
        <div class="sig-line"></div>
        <div class="sig-line-label">Date</div>
